2.187','2025-11-12','[\"Hi\\n\\n2 matters please;\\n\\n1. We want to upgrade and change our prattgroup.co.nz email accounts.\\n\\n2. We also have a spark/xtra email account \'prattharvestltd@xtra.co.nz\', that we want to have forwarded to accounts@prattgroup.co.nz\\n\\nCan you please advise how we can go about doing this.\\n\\nI have logged into our pratt account under this login, but my email is david.linstrom@prattgroup.co.nz\\n\\nRegards\\n\\nDavid\", \"4 hours ago\\n from IP 121.79.232.187\"]','[\"Hi David,\\n\\nThank you for reaching out to us.\\n\\nRegarding your requests:\\n\\nUpgrading and Changing Email Accounts (prattgroup.co.nz):\\nWe have two available email plan options you can choose from, depending on your business needs:\\n\\nBusiness Email: https://domainz.net.nz/business-email\\n\\nProfessional Email: https://domainz.net.nz/professional-email\\n\\nBoth plans include secure, reliable hosting with modern webmail access and synchronization across multiple devices. You can review the features and pricing from the links above and let us know which plan best suits your requirements. Once confirmed, we‚Äôll guide you through the upgrade process and ensure a smooth transition.\\n\\nForwarding Spark/Xtra Email (prattharvestltd@xtra.co.nz):\\nSince this email address is hosted with another provider, forwarding needs to be set up from within that account‚Äôs webmail or settings. However, we can provide step-by-step guidance to help you configure forwarding so that all messages are sent automatically to accounts@prattgroup.co.nz.\\n\\nRegards,\\nIwan\", \"a few seconds ago\\n from IP 202.58.196.49\"]','cmhty86rl0000ooon6j5qix5j','2025-11-12 01:16:45.955','2025-11-12 01:34:45.629','https://admin.worldhost.group/admin/support/inbox/3e8d569d-0724-563d-1178-ad4e85312160?_gl=1%2algbp8p%2a_up%2aMQ..%2a_ga%2aMTQxOTg1NDkzMC4xNzYyOTAyMjYz%2a_ga_KLRWZFRZE4%2aczE3NjI5MDIyNjIkbzEkZzEkdDE3NjI5MDI5ODUkajYwJGwwJGgw'),('BGP-504-90349__day__2025-11-12','FastComet','LUIS AGUILAR','Inquiry about migrating to VPS Cloud 3','Iwan Setiawan','Product','Awaiting Response','an hour ago\n from IP 2800:200:ff80:576:3079:1c2a:f41b:ef2a','2025-11-12','[\"Hello,\\n\\nI‚Äôm interested in migrating my current hosting service to a VPS Cloud 3 plan with you.\\nBefore making a decision, I‚Äôd like to clarify a few questions:\\n\\nWhat is the practical difference between a Managed VPS and an Unmanaged VPS?\\n\\nWhat are the advantages and disadvantages of each option in terms of control, support, and server maintenance?\\n\\nWith a Managed VPS, will I have full root access or limited privileges?\\n\\nIf root access is limited, what type of tasks would I be able to perform, and which ones would be restricted?\\n\\nCan you help me migrate all my websites and databases from my current hosting account? Approximately how long would the migration process take?\\n\\nDo you handle the DNS configuration, or do I need to manage that with my current domain provider?\\n\\nHow long does DNS propagation usually take after the change?\\n\\nOn a Managed VPS, is it possible to install other languages or environments (for example, Node.js, Python, etc.)?\\n\\nCan I install additional services such as Redis, Elasticsearch, or Docker?\\n\\nOn an Unmanaged VPS, would it be possible to purchase and use cPanel?\\n\\nIs the VPS fully dedicated, or are some resources shared with other clients?\\n\\nLastly, I would like to know the pricing for both the Managed and Unmanaged VPS options.\\n\\nI‚Äôve been working with FastComet since 2021, and as a loyal customer, I‚Äôd like to ask if it would be possible to receive a discount for this upgrade.\\n\\nThank you very much for your time and assistance ‚Äî I‚Äôll be waiting for your reply.\\n\\nBest regards,\\nLuis Aguilar\", \"an hour ago\\n from IP 2800:200:ff80:576:3079:1c2a:f41b:ef2a\"]','[\"Hi Luis,\\n\\nThank you for reaching out and for your continued trust since 2021. We truly appreciate your loyalty to FastComet. I‚Äôd be glad to clarify your questions about our VPS Cloud 3 plan and the difference between Managed and Unmanaged VPS options.\\n\\n1. Managed vs. Unmanaged VPS\\n\\nManaged VPS\\nOur technical team fully maintains the server for you. This includes software updates, security, performance tuning, backups, and 24/7 monitoring. You can focus on running your websites and development while we take care of the server‚Äôs health and uptime.\\n\\n2. Unmanaged VPS\\nYou get full root access and complete control over the server configuration, but you are responsible for all maintenance tasks, software installation, updates, security patches, and troubleshooting.\\n\\n3. Control, Support, and Maintenance\\n\\nManaged VPS: Full support from our SysAdmin team with proactive monitoring, automatic backups, and priority technical assistance. Root access is not available for stability and security, but you will have full WHM/cPanel access for website management.\\n\\nUnmanaged VPS: Full root access and complete freedom to configure the server as you wish, but no active management or monitoring from our side. Support is limited to hardware and network availability.\\n\\n4. Root Access and Permissions\\n\\nOn a Managed VPS, root access is not available to prevent conflicts with the server management layer. You‚Äôll still be able to:\\n\\nManage websites, databases, and email accounts through WHM/cPanel.\\n\\nCreate new accounts, install SSLs, and adjust PHP versions.\\n\\nHowever, you won‚Äôt be able to:\\n\\nModify core OS or kernel settings.\\n\\nInstall custom software that may interfere with our management configuration.\\n\\nOn an Unmanaged VPS, you‚Äôll have full root access with no restrictions.\\n\\n5. Website & Database Migration\\nYes, we‚Äôll be happy to handle the full migration of your websites, databases, and email accounts from your current hosting account. The duration depends on the total data size.\\n\\n6. DNS Configuration & Propagation\\nWe can assist you with DNS configuration d