eed assistance with the process, feel free to reach out. We\'re here to help.\\n\\nBest regards,\\nIvan\", \"7 hours ago\\n from IP 103.18.65.51\", \"Name: Joel Marsh (MARSH PROPERTY HOLDINGS PTY LTD)\\nProduct/Domain Name: .com.au (jmlandscapedesign.com.au)\\nEmail Address: design@jmlandscapedesign.com.au\\nPhone Number: +61 422029123\\nTicket: ND-BMB-925-59644\\nUpmind Link: https://admin.worldhost.group/admin/clients/381d780e-72d4-d129-58d9-c7413569926e/overview\\nIssue: Client would like to extend payment extension for 4 weeks.\\nResolution/Action Taken: Informed client that we are unable to extend payments with domain names.\", \"7 hours ago\\n from IP 103.18.65.51\", \"Hi Joel,\\n\\nThank you for reaching billing support.\\n\\nWe understand that flexibility with payment deadlines can be important, and we truly empathize with your situation. However, please allow us to explain why payment extensions are not typically possible when it comes to domain names.\\n\\nDomain renewals are processed in real-time through global domain registries, which are the official organizations responsible for managing domain name systems worldwide. Once a domain is renewed, the registry immediately applies the renewal and marks it as active. This process is automated and irreversible.\\n\\nBecause of this real-time, non-reversible nature, domain providers like us must collect payment upfront and cannot delay or extend payment deadlines. We are required to follow strict registry rules to ensure domain ownership is maintained and that no disruption occurs in your domain‚Äôs availability.\\n\\nThis is not a policy unique to our platform‚Äîit is an industry-wide standard enforced by all accredited domain registrars.\\n\\nWe hope this provides clarity, and we‚Äôre more than happy to assist you with any alternative solutions or answer further questions you may have.\\n\\nRegards,\\nIvan\", \"7 hours ago\\n from IP 103.18.65.51\"]','cmhty86rl0000ooon6j5qix5j','2025-11-13 03:56:50.418','20