'2025-11-13','[\"Good afternoon. Our organization co-director got a notice this morning that an email sent to her ilsr.org domain was blocked by the server, with a status code of 550 5.0.350. The sending email address comes from @nationalgrocers.org. Her email address is smitchell@ilsr.org. It sounds like there are other communications that our co-director is currently expecting to receive but has not, which may be related. Will someone look into this and get back to us as soon as possible? Happy to provide more info if needed. Thanks.\", \"2 hours ago\\n from IP 156.47.97.174\"]','[\"Hi there,\\n\\nThank you for contacting our support and for sharing the error screenshot.\\n\\nBased on the message, the sender at nationalgrocers.org (using Office 365) attempted to email smitchell@ilsr.org, but the message was rejected by the receiving server with status code 550 5.0.350. Since the ilsr.org domain uses Cloudflare for DNS and Google Workspace for email hosting, the rejection came directly from Google‚Äôs mail servers.\\n\\nAs the MX records and name servers for ilsr.org are not managed by us, we unfortunately do not have access to their Google Workspace environment or security policies. Because of this, we‚Äôre unable to review Google‚Äôs logs or adjust any settings that caused the message to be blocked.\\n\\nTo resolve this, the ilsr.org domain administrator will need to:\\n\\n‚Ä¢ Review the Google Workspace email security logs\\n‚Ä¢ Check whether the sender‚Äôs domain (nationalgrocers.org) is failing SPF, DKIM, or DMARC validation\\n‚Ä¢ Confirm that no filtering or security rules are blocking messages from Office 365\\n‚Ä¢ Review any Google Workspace ‚ÄúSpam‚Äù, ‚ÄúQuarantine‚Äù, or ‚ÄúRejected‚Äù policies applied to smitchell@ilsr.org\\n\\nIt may also help for the sender to verify that nationalgrocers.org has properly configured SPF, DKIM, and DMARC records, as Google often rejects messages that fail these checks.\\n\\nIf you can provide the full bounce-back messag