m IP 134.0.194.110\"]','[\"Hi there,\\n\\nThank you for your response.\\n\\nBy default, the email exchanger should not send duplicate emails. To verify and investigate this further, could you please send a test email from Webmail and check if the duplication still occurs?\\n\\nOnce the test email is sent, kindly provide the sender and recipient addresses so we can review the mail logs and confirm whether the duplication issue persists.\\n\\nRegards,\\nIwan\", \"a few seconds ago\\n from IP 202.58.196.49\", \"This ticket was unassigned due to inactivity. Here is a quick summary of what has happened so far:\\n\\nThe customer reported email duplication issues when sending a specific email (\\\"RE: API3242563 - UPDATED SOA AATCO\\\"). An agent explained that the issue likely stemmed from the server\'s handling of the email, particularly due to Exim\'s processing. The customer inquired about server tuning to prevent future duplications, while the agent suggested testing email sending via Webmail to determine if the problem lies with Outlook. The customer confirmed the issue only occurs with this specific email and requested further guidance on preventing it.\", \"27 minutes ago\\n from IP 192.250.239.172\", \"Previously consulted with L3, and he advised the client to try sending an email using webmail to see if the duplicate still happens.\", \"an hour ago\\n from IP 202.58.196.49\", \"Hi Prasad,\\n\\nThank you for your update. To help us isolate whether the duplication is caused by the Outlook client or the server, could you please try sending a test email directly from Webmail https://webmail.expressfreightoman.com using the same account (mahesh@expressfreightoman.com) to multiple recipients?\\n\\nIf the issue does not occur in Webmail, this would indicate the duplication is related to the Outlook client or its synchronization.\\n\\nKindly contact us if you need another help.\\n\\nKind regards,\\nAga\", \"an hour ago\\n from IP 202.58.196.49\", \"Hello Prasad,\\n\\nThe duplication of the \\\"RE: API3242563 - UPDATED SOA AATCO\\\" email looks to have been due to how Exim on the server handled the email.\\n\\nSince it contained a combination of local deliveries and external deliveries, Exim attempted the local deliveries, then the spam scanner ran on the email for external deliveries, and finally the spam scanner re-queued the email for the external deliveries following the scan. This caused 2 emails (the duplicates) to be queued for the kerry.com email addresses.\\n\\nThis was likely caused by a race condition requiring fairly specific circumstances, which explains why you have only been able to do this once.\\n\\nIf there\'s anything else we can assist you with, please feel free to reach out.\\n\\nThank you,\\nNicholas E.\", \"Nov 10th 21:31 PM\\n from IP 68.66.195.6\", \"Customer says, multiple recipients were added to the outgoing email they sent recently on Friday from mahesh@expressfreightoman.com.\\ncx confirms that he is not using any mailing list, contact forms.\\n------\\n\\ncheck if they are using any email client apps, or had any multiple recipients in outlook or any other similar app.\\nadvise password reset.\", \"Nov 10th 17:53 PM\\n from IP 68.66.195.6\", \"Hello Prasad,\\n\\nThank you for the update.\\n\\nWe‚Äôve reviewed the information, and it appears that the emails are being duplicated at the sending stage. Since this is not being triggered by any mailing list, contact form, or post comment form, we‚Äôd like to gather a few more details to isolate the cause.\\n\\nCould you please confirm the following:\\n- Are you sending the email through Outlook, Webmail, or a mobile email app?\\n- If using Outlook, please check if the Outbox contains multiple stuck copies of the same message ‚Äî sometimes Outlook retries sending automatically when there‚Äôs a temporary connection lag.\\n- Has this happened with multiple recipients or only specific ones?\\n- Please let us know if you have any email forwarding, auto-responder, 