ail address is with 20GB above the limit.\\n\\n\\nTo manage the storage space, I advise you to connect to your email address from a desktop computer and use a mail client like Thunderbird. Add your account to it and once all of your messages are synchronized, you can download them on your device using the Export function.\\n\\nOnce your emails are exported, you can remove the oldest ones, and this will further free space on your email account.\\n\\nWhen you have freed enough space and your email account us using less than 1 GB of storage, you can continue to use it with POP3 configurations and check on your device for any option that states \\\"Leave messages on server\\\"\\n\\nBest wishes,\\nNikolay St.\", \"Nov 11th 20:12 PM\\n from IP 94.156.219.172\", \"EOS surrendering\", \"Nov 11th 19:56 PM\\n from IP 185.149.115.6\", \"Hello Matthew,\\n\\nThank you for your patience.\\n\\nWe understand the frustration with the mailbox storage not reducing. We have confirmed that your device is connecting using POP, however the current configuration on the iPhone may be set to \'leave a copy of messages on the server\'. When this setting is enabled, emails remain stored on the server even after being downloaded, which prevents the disk usage from decreasing.\\n\\nCould you please review the POP settings on your iPhone by following the steps below:\\n\\nSettings > Mail > Accounts > Select your email account > Account > Advanced > \\\"Delete from Server\\\"\\n\\nOnce this setting is adjusted, new messages will be removed from the server after download, and the mailbox size will begin to reduce.\\n\\nThank you again for your understanding, and please let us know once the settings have been checked and changed.\\n\\nIf there‚Äôs anything else we can do for you, or if there is any other trouble, please don‚Äôt hesitate to write back. We‚Äôll be here to help.\\n\\nRegards,\\nSreevas M K\\nCustomer Care Representative\", \"Nov 11th 19:15 PM\\n from IP 185.149.115.6\", \"email is on a shared server, we are unable to increase the mailbox capacity\\nbut they should review their pop3 confiuration and if they are using iphone, they should have an option such as Settings ‚Üí Mail ‚Üí Accounts ‚Üí Select your account ‚Üí Account ‚Üí Advanced ‚Üí Delete from Server and setting it to delete messages right away.\\n\\nchecked in swarm. advising Customer\", \"Nov 11th 19:13 PM\\n from IP 185.149.115.6 \\n(edited by Sreevas M.)\", \"aigis.com.au\\ns3931.syd1.stableserver.net\\n\\nCustomer is frustrated due to email box being full. They are using iphone and have configured pop3, but space is not reducing\\n\\nchecked logs\\nThe user is logging in via POP:\\npop3-login: Login: user=<matthew@aigis.com.au>\\nDovecot tries to open the mailbox index files.\\nIt finds the index files are incomplete / corrupted:\", \"Nov 11th 18:59 PM\\n from IP 185.149.115.6\", \"Hello Matthew,\\n\\nThank you for your patience.\\n\\nWe are currently reviewing this case with our specialists to resolve the mailbox issue correctly. We will update you as soon as we have more information.\\n\\nIf you have any questions in the meantime, please feel free to reply. We are here to help.\\n\\nRegards,\\nSreevas M K\\nCustomer Care Representative\", \"Nov 11th 18:59 PM\\n from IP 185.149.115.6\", \"https://teams.microsoft.com/l/message/19:c94a9349f1b940be948302fd2610b65a@thread.tacv2/1762858682770?tenantId=ea8e08e3-9c7a-40c0-95ef-6ec0a852a961&groupId=fc2878a7-ff2a-475b-819a-d58a6e517b96&parentMessageId=1762858682770&teamName=Customer%20Care&channelName=Escalated%20Support&createdTime=1762858682770\", \"Nov 11th 18:58 PM\\n from IP 185.149.115.6\", \"Hello\\n\\nThank you for getting back to us and I am sorry to hear the disk space is not getting reduced.\\n\\nYou will need to switch the email setup to POP instead of IMAP.\\n\\nPOP downloads the emails to your computer and removes them from the server, which will free space permanently.\\n\\nWhat to do next:\\n\\nRemove the existing email account from your mail program\\n\\nRe-add it using POP with these settings:\\nIncoming Server: s3931.syd1.stableserver.net\\nProtocol: POP3\\nPort: 995 (SSL enabled)\\n\\nOutgoing Server: s3931.syd1.stableserver.net\\nPort: 465 (SSL enabled)\\n\\nOnce set to POP, emails will be stored on your device and space on the server will clear as new mail downloads.\\n\\nIf you should need any further assistance, feel free to contact us. We are available 24/7. Thank you!\\n\\nMeera E\\nCustomer Care Representative -L1\", \"Nov 11th 17:49 PM\\n from IP 68.66.252.42\", \"https://teams.microsoft.com/l/message/19:c94a9349f1b940be948302fd2610b65a@thread.tacv2/1762853333211?tenantId=ea8e08e3-9c7a-40c0-95ef-6ec0a852a961&groupId=fc2878a7-ff2a-475b-819a-d58a6e517b96&parentMessageId=1762853333211&teamName=Customer%20Care&channelName=Escalated%20Support&createdTime=1762853333211\", \"Nov 11th 17:29 PM\\n from IP 68.66.252.42\", \"Hello Matthew,\\n\\nThank you for getting back to us.\\n\\nI can see the disk usage on the account is still not reduced.\\n\\nPlease delete older/large-attachment emails from Inbox and Sent . Ensure to empty Trash/Deleted Items and also clear Junk/Spam if large.\\n\\nIf you should need any further assistance, feel free to contact us. We are available 24/7. Thank you!\\n\\nMeera E\\nCustomer Care Representative -L1\", \"Nov 11th 16:48 PM\\n from IP 68.66.252.42\", \"Hello Matthew,\\n\\nThank you for getting back to us.\\n\\nAt the moment, the mailbox cannot be accessed via Webmail because the account storage is completely full Disk Usage 20 GB / 20 GB (99.99%). When the storage reaches 100%, the server can no longer load Webmail, which is why you‚Äôre seeing the 500 error.\\n\\nI can see the inbox for the mail account matthew@aigis.com.au using the space.\\n\\nTo fix this, if you have IMAP account configured for the email account in your email client (e.g., Outlook / Apple Mail / Gmail app) then,\\n\\nOpen your email app where you normally access the mailbox.\\nDelete some older / large emails from the Inbox and Sent folders.\\nThen empty the Trash/Deleted Items folder from the same app.\\n\\nThis will free up the account storage and Webmail will start working again automatically once enough space is cleared.\\n\\nFeel free to contact us if you need any further assistance.\\n\\nMeera E\\nCustomer Care Representative -L1\", \"Nov 11th 14:06 PM\\n from IP 68.66.252.42\", \"This ticket was unassigned due to inactivity. Here is a quick summary of what has happened so far:\\n\\nThe customer, Matthew, reported an email server error. The agent informed him that the issue is due to reaching the account\'s disk usage limit (20 GB). To resolve this, Matthew needs to delete unnecessary emails or attachments to free up space. The agent offered further assistance if needed.\", \"Nov 11th 13:50 PM\\n from IP 192.250.239.172\", \"Hello Matthew,\\n\\nThank you for contacting us!\\n\\nWe have checked your account and found that your email service is showing a server error because your account disk usage has reached its limit. Your total disk usage is 20 GB / 20 GB (99.99%), with Email Accounts consuming approximately 21.22 GB.\\n\\nTo resolve this issue, please free up space by deleting unnecessary emails or attachments from your cPanel email account. Once sufficient space is available, your email service should function normally.\\n\\nWe remain available should you need any further assistance.\\n\\nKind Regards,\\nTeodora L.\", \"Nov 10th 17:09 PM\\n from IP 94.156.219.172\"]','cmhty86rl0000ooon6j5qix5j','2025-11-12 03:09:29.453','2025-11-12 03:09:49.353','https://admin.worldhost.group/admin/support/inbox/e071d931-d5e4-68d7-7983-c54602875839?_gl=1%2a1629xqe%2a_up%2aMQ..%2a_ga%2aMTUzNDU4MDA5Ny4xNzYyOTExMTg1%2a_ga_KLRWZFRZE4%2aczE3NjI5MTExODQkbzEkZzAkdDE3NjI5MTExODQkajYwJGwwJGgw'),('GUA-600-22034','hosting.com','Levin Associates','Server Issue','Iwan Setiawan','Server','Awaiting Response','Nov 10th 23:10 PM\n from IP 75.179.20.92','2025-11-11T