ause you to lose the current website that was built please reply to this ticket confirming if you would still like us to change the domain.\\n\\nIf you have any further questions, please respond directly to this and we will get back to you as soon as we can.\\n\\nThank you,\\nMichael W.\", \"Nov 12th 03:11 AM\\n from IP 68.66.195.6\", \"This ticket was unassigned due to inactivity. Here is a quick summary of what has happened so far:\\n\\nDonna reported an issue with changing her domain from mrocanada.org to dillonoconnor.ca after purchasing the new domain. Agent Christian acknowledged the problem and created a ticket for further investigation, assuring Donna that a specialist will provide updates soon.\", \"Nov 12th 01:50 AM\\n from IP 192.250.239.172\"]','cmhty86rl0000ooon6j5qix5j','2025-11-13 01:03:20.279','2025-11-13 01:49:39.518','https://admin.worldhost.group/admin/support/inbox/3e8d569d-0724-563d-6769-fd4e85312160'),('KMA-945-50017','Webcentral','Jill ILIFFE','SSL installation on domain unitsplan439.org','Iwan Setiawan','Website','Awaiting Response','3 hours ago\n from IP 45.118.67.135','2025-11-11T07:26:15.292Z','[\"Dear Okbar G\\n\\nI would you prefer to wait for the Let‚Äôs Encrypt rate limit to reset before we reinstall the SSL from cPanel? Do you know how long that will take?\\n\\nAlso, if the expiry comes after 90 days, what do I have to do to make sure this does not happen again. I don‚Äôt remember anyone telling me I had to renew every 90 days? Is that because it is free? Is there some way of installing an SSL certificate so that it does not have to renew every 90 days even if there is a cost?\\n\\nYour advice appreciated, thanks. Jill\\n\\n\\n\\nFrom: Webcentral Support <support@webcentral.au>\\nSent: Tuesday, November 11, 2025 4:21 PM\\nTo: Jill ILIFFE <jilliliffe@gmail.com>\\nSubject: New Support Ticket Message - WCG-KMA-945-50017 - SSL installation on domain unitsplan439.org\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n<https://theconsole.webcentral.au/login>\\n\\n\\n\\nHi J