icket was unassigned due to inactivity. Here is a quick summary of what has happened so far:\\n\\nSafi inquired about adding a subdomain and reported that the subdomain app.foi-fgi.com was not working after installation. Miroslav advised that the main domain is using Cloudflare and instructed Safi to add the domain in Cloudflare, pointing the A record to the specified IP address. Safi confirmed the record was added and asked if further action was needed. The ticket is focused on DNS configuration and subdomain functionality.\", \"7 hours ago\\n from IP 192.250.239.172\", \"Hello Safi,\\n\\nThank you for your reply.\\n\\nUpon careful investigation I can see the main domain foi-fgi.com is using Cloudflare. In such cases you need to add the domain also from your Cloudflare account and point its A record to IP address 139.162.149.129. Allow me to explain a bit more:\\n\\nWhen a different service is used to maintain the DNS for the domain, a new subdomain has to be added also from there. Kindly note any DNS change is subject to propagation time of at most 24 to 48 hours. Once over, the changes should reflect, and the subdomain should load.\\n\\nPlease let us know if there is anything else we can help you with.\\n\\nMiroslav T.\\nSupport Generalist\", \"8 hours ago\\n from IP 68.66.195.6\", \"CX created a subdomain app. foi-fgi.com but it is not working\\n\\nCF is being used so the subdomain has to be added also from CF http://leafdns.com/index.cgi?testid=95E654C7\", \"8 hours ago\\n from IP 68.66.195.6\", \"Hello Abdulfettah,\\n\\nYou can do this from the Domains page in cPanel. There you will see an Add a New Domain button. From there you can add subdomains on the account as well.\\n\\nRegards,\\nGeorgi G.\", \"Nov 10th 21:16 PM\\n from IP 77.95.113.232\"]','cmhty86rl0000ooon6j5qix5j','2025-11-11 02:37:53.034','2025-11-11 05:10:05.624',NULL),('TVB-932-13385__day__2025-11-13','Mochahost','Danilo Novaes','Configuration Mail','Iwan Setiawan','Email','Awaiting Response','3 hours ago\n from IP 2804:14c:174:489c:a5d3:234b:566f:fa7c','2025-11-13','[\"I am configuring the mail sending service and would like to know the parameters for.\\n\\nsmptClint:\\nport:\\n\\nbecause I have this information but it is not sending.\\n\\nMail server username\\naviso@sensurix.com\\n\\nOutgoing mail server (requires authentication)\\nsensurix.com\\n\\nIncoming mail server\\nsensurix.com\\n\\nSupported outgoing mail protocols\\nSMTP\\n\\nSupported incoming mail protocols\\nPOP3, IMAP\\n\\nsmtp:465\\nimap:993\\npop3:995\", \"3 hours ago\\n from IP 2804:14c:174:489c:a5d3:234b:566f:fa7c\"]','[\"Hi there,\\n\\nThank you for contacting our support.\\n\\nBased on the information provided, here are the correct mail settings you should use for your email configuration:\\n\\nUsername\\naviso@sensurix.com\\n\\nOutgoing mail server (SMTP)\\nmail.sensurix.com\\nPort: 465\\nEncryption: SSL/TLS\\nAuthentication: Required\\n\\nIncoming mail server (IMAP or POP3)\\nmail.sensurix.com\\n\\nIMAP\\nPort: 993\\nEncryption: SSL/TLS\\n\\nPOP3\\nPort: 995\\nEncryption: SSL/TLS\\n\\nPlease make sure the following are enabled in your mail client:\\n‚Ä¢ Use SSL/TLS encryption\\n‚Ä¢ Outgoing server requires authentication\\n‚Ä¢ Username is the full email address (aviso@sensurix.com)\\n\\nIf you still cannot send or receive emails after applying these settings, please let us know the exact error message so we can assist you further.\\n\\nRegards,\\nIwan\", \"a few seconds ago\\n from IP 202.58.196.49\"]','cmhty86rl0000ooon6j5qix5j','2025-11-13 00:45:42.657','2025-11-13 00:46:43.326','https://admin.worldhost.group/admin/support/inbox/1e509897-3d24-7510-6093-f345e610832d?_gl=1%2a12ac5lc%2a_up%2aMQ..%2a_ga%2aMjEwOTAzMTk3My4xNzYyOTg4ODIz%2a_ga_KLRWZFRZE4%2aczE3NjI5OTI2MDUkbzIkZzAkdDE3NjI5OTI2MDUkajYwJGwwJGgw'),('UDY-826-36716','hosting.com','Juan Andr√©s Barbosa Fajardo','Use email tool with new domain','Iwan Setiawan','Email','Client replied','8 hours ago\n from IP 2800:484:5088:6e00:c891:1ebf:df91:e2cd','2025-11-11T03:10:27.031Z','[\"Thank you for your response.\\n\\nOne additional question, I have the new website hosted on Google Cloud, and I had to point the domain to Google\'s CNAME (ghs.googlehosted.com).\\nShould I follow this procedure as you explain it so that it only works for email here at a2hosting using my current plan?\\n\\nWon\'t this interfere with Google hosting?\\n\\nThank you.\", \"6 minutes ago\\n from IP 2800:484:5088:6e00:48a9:70e5:5bd6:49bd\", \"Hello Iwan, thanks for your reply.\\n\\nI will like to use my current webmail service, could you guide me please.\\n\\nThanks and regards,\\nJuan\", \"31 minutes ago\\n from IP 2800:484:5088:6e00:48a9:70e5:5bd6:49bd\", \"Hello, I have a new domain with GoDaddy and would like to have a professional email address. What can I do to use the email tool with this new domain within the plan I already have with you?\", \"8 hours ago\\n from IP 2800:484:5088:6e00:c891:1ebf:df91:e2cd\"]','[\"Hi there,\\n\\nThank you for your response.\\n\\nTo create a new email address using your new domain, please follow the steps below:\\n\\n1. Add your new domain to cPanel\\n\\nLog in to your cPanel account.\\n\\nGo to Domains ‚Üí Add Domain and enter your new domain name.\\n\\nThis will link your domain to your hosting account.\\n\\n2. Update your domain name servers\\n\\nLog in to your domain registrar (for example, GoDaddy, Namecheap, etc.).\\n\\nUpdate the name servers to point to your cPanel hosting:\\n\\nns1.a2hosting.com\\nns2.a2hosting.com\\nns3.a2hosting.com\\nns4.a2hosting.com\\n\\n\\nOnce updated, please allow up to 24 hours for DNS propagation.\\n\\n3. Create your new email address\\n\\nAfter the domain is connected, return to your cPanel.\\n\\nGo to Email Accounts ‚Üí Create.\\n\\nChoose your new domain from the drop-down menu, then enter your desired email address (for example, info@yourdomain.com) and password.\\n\\n4. Access your webmail\\n\\nOnce created, you can log in to your mailbox by visiting:\\nhttps://yourdomain.com/webmail\\n\\nAlternatively, you can configure the new mailbox in your preferred email client (Outlook, Apple Mail, Gmail, etc.) using the mail server settings provided in cPanel.\\n\\nIf you‚Äôd like, we can assist you by verifying your DNS and confirming that your domain is properly connected before you create the email. Please let us know once you‚Äôve updated the name servers or if you‚Äôd prefer us to check them for you.\\n\\nRegards,\\nIwan\", \"21 minutes ago\\n from IP 202.58.196.49\", \"Hi Juan,\\n\\nThank you for contacting our support.\\n\\nI understand that you have a new domain registered with GoDaddy and would like to set up a professional email address using your existing hosting plan with us.\\n\\nCurrently, your plan includes a cPanel hosting service, which already provides access to webmail where you can create and manage email accounts using your domain (for example, info@yourdomain.com). If you‚Äôd like, we can guide you through setting up a new mailbox under your existing hosting account so you can start sending and receiving emails right away.\\n\\nAlternatively, if you prefer a more advanced and dedicated email platform with enhanced security, storage, and collaboration tools, you may also consider our Email Hosting plans, which are separate from your web hosting. You can explore the available options here:\\nhttps://hosting.com/hosting/hosting-by-service/email-hosting/\\n\\nPlease confirm whether you‚Äôd like to use your current webmail service or set up a new professional email hosting plan. Once confirmed, we‚Äôll provide the exact steps to configure your email with the new domain.\\n\\nRegards,\\nIwan\", \"2 hours ago\\n from IP 202.58.196.49\"]','cmhty86rl0000ooon6j5qix5j','2025-11-11 02:38:08.717','2025-11-11 05:11:13.357',NULL),('URI-571-84329','Webcentral','Adam Mooney','Cannot create simple email','Iwan Setiawan','Email','Awaiting Response','2 hours ago\n from IP 110.150.70.57','2025-11-11T03:47:34.868Z','[\"I am still being billed for the M365 Simple Email plan - am I correct that there is one existing mailbox \\\"admin@awmooneycomau.onmicrosoft.com\\\" tied to that plan?\\n\\nBefore I upgrade and create a new basic mailbox, can that mailbox be edited, altered or re-named?\", \"39 minutes ago\\n from IP 110.150.70.57\", \"Hi there, I have subscriptions to both simple email and standard M365 on my domain. I want to create a new simple email address (i.e. it does not need access to the whole M365 suite, it just needs to be able to receive emails). I cannot find a way to set up that simple address without assigning a standard license.\\n\\nIs it possible to have just a simple email address without needing to assign it a full standard license? If not, is there any point in me having both?\", \"2 hours ago\\n from IP 110.150.70.57\"]','[\"Hi Adam,\\n\\nThank you for your reply.\\n\\nUpon checking, it seems that admin@awmooneycomau.onmicrosoft.com is a default address automatically created when your domain was first assigned to the Microsoft 365 service. This account acts as a default administrative user for the tenancy.\\n\\nTo create your own custom email address (for example, info@yourdomain.com or yourname@yourdomain.com), please log in to the Microsoft 365 Admin https://theconsole.webcentral.au/products/contracts/831d6350-d824-9028-9983-c849e176259e/product/0d1639e2-37d4-3978-067d-b64610589e57. From there, you can add a user and create a new mailbox using your domain name. You can refer to the attached screenshot for guidance.\\n\\nOnce you‚Äôve created the new user, you can then assign the new Microsoft 365 license to that mailbox. This will activate email functionality for the new address and allow you to send and receive mail normally.\\n\\nPlease let us know once the new address has been created or if you‚Äôd like assistance during the setup process.\\n\\nRegards,\\nIwan\", \"a few seconds ago\\n from IP 202.58.196.49\", \"This ticket was unassigned due to inactivity. Here is a quick summary of what has happened so far:\\n\\nThe customer inquired about being billed for the M365 Simple Email plan and asked if the existing mailbox \\\"admin@awmooneycomau.onmicrosoft.com\\\" could be edited or renamed. The agent clarified that the Simple Email plan is legacy, preventing new mailboxes from being created. To create a new basic mailbox, the customer must upgrade to Exchange Online Plan 1, which will increase their monthly charge. The customer is considering whether to proceed with the upgrade.\", \"15 minutes ago\\n from IP 192.250.239.172\", \"Hello\\n\\nThanks for the details.\\n\\n\\\"M365 Simple Email‚Äù is a legacy plan Microsoft no longer offers. Because of that, no new mailboxes can be created under this plan‚Äîhence it shows 0 available.\\n\\nYou currently have adam@awmooney.com.au on Microsoft 365 Business Standard.\\n\\nTo create a new basic mailbox (email-only, no Office apps), the simple Email plans should be upgraded to Exchange Online Plan 1 (P1) for that mailbox.\\n\\nPricing:\\n\\nCurrent charge: A$10.48 / month\\nThis will increase to A$13.10 / month starting from the 5 Dec 2025 ‚Äì 5 Jan 2026 billing period onward.\\n\\nPlease let me know whether you would like to proceed with upgrade.\\n\\nMeera E\\nCustomer Care Representative -L1\", \"an hour ago\\n from IP 68.66.252.42\", \"https://teams.microsoft.com/l/message/19:c94a9349f1b940be948302fd2610b65a@thread.tacv2/1762826926566?tenantId=ea8e08e3-9c7a-40c0-95ef-6ec0a852a961&groupId=fc2878a7-ff2a-475b-819a-d58a6e517b96&parentMessageId=1762826926566&teamName=Customer%20Care&channelName=Escalated%20Support&createdTime=1762826926566\", \"2 hours ago\\n from IP 68.66.252.42\"]','cmhty86rl0000ooon6j5qix5j','2025-11-11 03:47:35.609','2025-11-11 05:11:16.236',NULL),('VJJ-954-62253','hosting.com','IT Department','WHM credentials','Iwan Setiawan','Server','Awaiting Response','8 hours ago\n from IP 2600:8800:7320:d200:cd8:8d31:caf:4cdc','2025-11-11T02:30:07.888Z','[\"Hi, we